Rating: 3
I liked this, but if I were to make it again, I would do a few things differently. First, while I think that boiling the beets was a quick and easy way to cook them, I would probably roast them in order to get a better flavor. The onions take 40 minutes to cook, so what's 50 for the beets to roast? I would then cut them into smaller pieces. I might roast the garlic along with it, but I might do it the same way as I did this time. This time, by the way, was not exactly how the recipe said to do it. I felt that the garlic would have burned had I added the beet greens and then covered the pan, so I deglazed with white whine first, and I figure that probably helped to tenderize the beet greens. The pine nuts were perfect, particularly if you manage not to burn them like I ALWAYS do. I think that goat cheese would probably be a better cheese than Parmesan, and I might try it next time. This dish might even be really yummy with some bacon, prosciutto or pancetta, but that would turn a relatively healthy dish into a not-so-healthy one.

